pysum - A pygtk application for create and verify md5 and other checksum
------------------------------------------------------------------------


pysum depends on the Python runtime and associated libraries.

Python (>= 2.5) : http://www.python.org
PyGTK (>= 2.8) : http://www.pygtk.org


== Licence ==

It's licensed under the GNU General Public License version 2, or
(at your option) any later version. See the COPYING file for details.


== To run Source code (without installing) ==

You can find the source code of pysum in /src. To run (without
installing), in a terminal use the following syntax:

$ cd src
$ python pysum.py


== To install ==

If you use debian, ubuntu, or some other similar, please using
the .deb package to install pySum.

For more detailed instructions (and generic installation
instructions), please see the INSTALL file.


== Translations (i18n/gettext) ==

Please view the instructions in the INSTALL file and /po directory

If you want to help translate pySum, please visit:
https://translations.launchpad.net/pysum
